article.headline: Rhode Island 65, Dayton 64
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Marquis Jones hit a 3-pointer with 5 seconds left to lift Rhode Island to a 65-64 win over Dayton on Tuesday night, snapping the Flyers' 30-game home winning streak. Jones also scored the game-winning buzzer-beater last year in the Rams' 93-91 overtime win over Dayton. Delroy James led Rhode Island (16-3, 4-2 Atlantic 10 Conference) with 22 points and Keith Cothran added 17. The Rams trailed 33-24 at halftime and by 11 with 18:26 left, but pulled ahead 45-44 on a Cothran three-point play. After Rhode Island extended its lead to 54-49 with 7:49 left, Dayton (14-6, 3-3) went on a 10-0 run. The Rams regained the advantage at 62-61 with 30 seconds left. Chris Johnson hit three straight free throws with 15 seconds remaining before Jones' game-winner. Mickey Perry's 3-pointer missed with 1 second left. Chris Wright and London Warren scored 12 each for the Flyers.
